@afterlifepress  AFTERLIFE is beyond proud to announce our newest publication series, DISINTEGRATION: tattoo inspiration in print. Each issue includes in-depth interviews with today’s leading tattooers—conversations about art, tattooing and life—as well as original essays by historians and artists. DISINTEGRATION aims to shed light on tattooing’s histories and lineages while also showcasing artists of all ages and backgrounds. By creating print volumes that explore these aspects of tattooing, we hope to recreate the magic of tattooing magazines and books of the past—publications that are increasingly rare today. Issue 1 ft @waterstreetphantom @gakkinx @victorjwebster @tamarasantibanez @codonnell_nyc @timothyhoyer @thomdevita

Over the last 1.5 years @afterlifepress and myself have been hard at work trying to bring a new series to the tattoo community. When I started tattooing and started spending time @fourstartattoonm it was instilled in me from day one the importance of books and documentation in tattooing. I was handed Tattoo time by Ed Hardy and told to read those and come back next week. I was 16 years old. I never looked back. Since then other magazines and publications have come out but nothing that ever evokes that same excitement that I felt when I was younger. The goal of DISINTEGRATION is to give us just that. Articles on tattooing, conversations about art and inspiration, interviews with outstanding tattooers and artists. Interviews done by some of the worlds best!! All for a low cost tattoo publication. So this is our first go at it. Let me know what you think! I think it’s one of the best things @afterlifepress has made and we are already deep into issues 2/3/4! You can find it at the link in my bio or @afterlifepress @blackclaw!
